  "title": "CONSTRUCTION MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Oversees and manages all site construction activities for LTA civil infrastructure projects, ensuring works are executed safely, on schedule, within quality standards, and in compliance with LTA requirements.<br /><br /><strong>Essential Job Functions:</strong></p><p>The Construction Manager is responsible for, but not limited to, the following:</p><ul><li>Lead and supervise the site construction team, including engineers, supervisors, and subcontractors.</li><li>Review and prepare method statements for submission to the client.</li><li>Manage a construction project team and oversee the construction activities, planning, implementation, and monitoring of work schedules in accordance with the master and detailed construction program.</li><li>Ensure progress according to schedule, quality standards are maintained site inspections are carried out and technical issues are resolved on time.</li><li>Monitor ongoing site activities and ensure work runs smoothly.</li><li>Liaise and coordinate with clients, designers, consultants, subcontractors, and different authorities on the project’s activities.</li><li>Track progress, prepare site reports, and support project management in planning and resource allocation.</li><li>Oversee materials, equipment, and manpower utilization to ensure efficiency.</li><li>Ensure safe work practices and lead site safety culture.</li><li>To perform Ad-Hoc duties as per assigned.</li></ul>",
